(323, 'analytic', 'excerpt', 1, 'en', 'Over the past 4 years, the total volume of imports of electronic products has increased by 49%, amounting in monetary terms to more than 336 billion tenge.', '2022-01-26 07:56:11', '2022-02-08 04:12:41'),
(324, 'analytic', 'first_content', 1, 'en', '<p>Today, the domestic IT industry has already gained critical mass for the implementation of new breakthrough projects of both national and international scale.<br />Infocommunication services, production of computer equipment, servers, telecommunications, network equipment, data processing centers and production of special equipment are sufficiently developed in the country.<br /><br /><strong>Smartphoneization of doctors in the Republic of Kazakhstan</strong><br /><br />Mobile devices began to be used to automate business processes long before the advent of current smartphones and tablets. About 20 years ago, mobile terminals came into use in large warehouses and logistics companies<br />With the advent of productive mobile devices, the range of companies equipping their employees with mobile devices to solve their specific tasks has expanded.<br />Specialized mobile applications are used by banks and other credit organizations. With their help, the work of repair teams servicing ATMs and terminals is coordinated, they are needed to serve customers in the field.<br />Mobile solutions are also in demand in education and medicine (for example, applications for emergency doctors and hospitals).<br /><br /><strong>Smartphone for doctors</strong><br />On the Medscape resource, Doctor of Medicine Bruno S. Oliveira, a practicing rheumatologist from the Billings Clinic, USA, shared with colleagues interesting information about which software applications for a smartphone can facilitate and optimize the work of a doctor. According to him, the rapid progress in the field of mobile technologies can and should be used by doctors for self-study, work with documentation and record keeping, as well as improving the efficiency of working with patients (reading medical news and magazines, assessing disease activity, calculating risks, decoding laboratory data, maintaining accounts, mobile access to their own files, time management).<br />A survey conducted by Cell Hearth Insight and M3 Research showed that 80% of doctors use smartphones in professional fields.<br />Mostly this happens to communicate with colleagues. Doctors consider communication via a smartphone to be faster and more convenient, since you can quickly send a message or find out any information.<br />In addition, the smartphone is also used to quickly obtain information from Wikipedia-type resources. It is interesting that most of the doctors, working at a computer, send messages through a smartphone, preferring it as a quick means of communication.<br />The share of doctors using smartphones and mobile phones to access professional information via the Internet has grown by 7.6% in two years and reached 72.6% of the total number of outpatient doctors surveyed.<br />The largest part of doctors &ndash; almost 45% - use both stationary computers and mobile platforms to access the Internet; 14% of doctors do not use a computer to search for professional information, making do exclusively with mobile devices (according to the fall 2018 Medi-Q survey \"Opinion of Practicing Physicians\" by Ipsos Comcon).<br />TOP 10 best solutions that can meet the needs of physicians: from students to practitioners:<br />Epocrates is an ersatz application for physicians. It contains reference books for doctors of various profiles, explanations for medicines, the identifier of tablets, medical news.<br />Figure 1 - Medical Images is a godsend for doctors and nurses. There is a visual archive collected here, i.e. a lot of images that will be useful in the diagnosis of diseases.<br />Doctor Booster is a professional tool for modern doctors. With this application, the work of a doctor is simplified at times! After all, from now on, all the most important things are in a smartphone or tablet and always at hand: medical histories, remote sending for tests, creating templates to save time, electronic appointments, appointment schedules, statistics, medical reference books and classifiers ICD-10, ICPC-2, creating medical events.<br />Medical Terminologies is a reference guide where all medical terms are collected.<br />Read by QxMD - gives access to specialized literature, current research, and the latest reviews.<br />UpToDate is a great way to keep track of medical news and achievements.<br />DailyRounds Doctor\'s App - the program provides access to a large medical network created exclusively for doctors to share experiences and news from the world of medicine.<br />Skyscape is one of the tools for the regions of our planet where there is no regular medical care, created by Health eVillages. This app is suitable for doctors, nurses, medical students and other medical professionals.<br />Isabel is an assistant application for diagnostics. With its help, a practicing doctor can double-check the diagnosis. subscription.<br />Medscape is an informative resource that can be equated to a universal medical reference book.</p>', '2022-01-26 07:56:11', '2022-02-08 04:12:41'),
(325, 'analytic', 'second_content', 1, 'en', '<p><strong>The smartphone will become the main medical gadget</strong><br />Larisa Popovich, Director of the Institute of Health Economics of the Higher School of Economics, stated that the telecommunications revolution has led to unprecedented openness of patients: according to a survey of the HSE, which was attended by about 4 thousand medical workers from all subjects of the Russian Federation, 72% of Russians aged 18-44 years are ready to communicate with their attending physician from home, and not in his office; 60% of patients plan to use video communication via a mobile device for these purposes. For their part, 81% of the surveyed doctors said that mobile access to medical records helps coordinate medical care, 58% of health workers are ready to provide some services remotely, and 38% of doctors already use email to be in contact with patients with chronic diseases all the time.<br />Telemedicine technologies should become an everyday tool, \"It is important that a person who has received medical care in a hospital, while on outpatient treatment, has the opportunity to stay in touch with his doctor all the time.\"<br />Personal data protection<br />However, the introduction of IT into daily medical practice is complicated by the fact that two generations of users are facing today: \"digital immigrants\" and \"digital aborigines\". Accordingly, two strategies are needed: in the first case, it is necessary to explain the inevitability of the digital age and teach elementary user skills, in the second - to instill skills of personal information security and network ethics.<br />Another difficulty is ensuring the security of users\' personal data in accordance with the law.<br />It is unacceptable for this information to fall into the hands of third parties and be used unlawfully. For this reason, you should use only securely protected information transmission channels or request a receipt from the patient about the permissibility of transmitting data about him over an open network.<br /><br /><strong>Available solutions on the Kazakhstan market</strong><br />Hospitals are overcrowded and doctors are unavailable: online medicine in Kazakhstan is becoming an urgent necessity. Previously, Kazakhstanis could attach themselves to a polyclinic through the eGov portal, make an appointment or call a doctor at home. Now, in connection with the quarantine, new services are appearing where the doctor will \"take\" you through a smartphone and prescribe the necessary medications. What are these services:<br /><br /><strong>Doctor Online from Beeline</strong><br />Telecom operator Beeline has introduced a new mobile application Doctor Online. Any resident of Kazakhstan can use the application, regardless of the mobile operator. You just need to download the app.<br />Mobi Doctor by Kcell<br />You can get an online consultation of the on-duty general practitioner or pediatrician in the mobile application or on the website mobidoctor.kcell.kz . The service works for kcell and activ subscribers seven days a week, anywhere in the world, at any time of the day or night. It will continue to work after the end of the pandemic.<br />Russian doctors consult on Mobi Doctor. They get in touch within a few minutes in the format of a chat, audio or video call and answer questions about the health of an adult patient or child. The duration of the consultation is about 30 minutes.<br /><br />Platform iDoctor.kz<br />The Ministry of Health of the Republic of Kazakhstan and the Ministry of Digital Development, Innovation and Aerospace Industry together with the Chocofamily Holding presented the launch of a new service of free online consultations with polyclinic doctors on the platform iDoctor.kz .<br />The service eliminates the need to go to the hospital and sit in queues. Without leaving home, a person can talk to his doctor via video link, exchange files, get a transcript of tests and appointments. Consultations will be conducted by doctors of a medical institution to which a citizen is attached within the framework of the state volume of free medical care (GOBMP).<br />Telegram bot \"Doctors Online / COVID\"<br />For remote consultation of patients on COVID-19, the Telegram bot \"Doctors Online / COVID\" works.</p>', '2022-01-26 07:56:11', '2022-02-08 04:17:52'),
(326, 'analytic', 'third_content', 1, 'en', '<p><strong>Offers</strong><br />It is proposed to equip doctors in the Republic of Kazakhstan with smartphones, while providing a comprehensive solution.<br />The integrated solution includes the provision of a smartphone, which will include the tariff plan \"Doctor\" with appropriate protection of personal data.<br />According to official data, the number of medical workers in the healthcare system amounted to 253,883 people, of which 74,046 are doctors, 179,837 are secondary medical personnel, while there is a shortage of doctors.<br />To provide 74,046 doctors in the Republic of Kazakhstan, it is necessary to allocate 6,844 million tenge from the republican budget or attract an international loan (90 thousand tenge + taking into account the tariff). To reduce the burden on the budget, the purchase can be divided into 3 years for 2,281 million tenge.<br />At the same time, the smartphone will be allocated to each doctor once every three years.<br /><br /><strong>Advantages of smartphone doctors in the Republic of Kazakhstan</strong></p>\n<p><strong><img src=\"http://itprom.testkz.ru/storage/analytic/February2022/1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"816\" height=\"523\" /></strong></p>\n<p><strong><img src=\"http://itprom.testkz.ru/storage/analytic/February2022/2.png\" alt=\"\" /></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Local content<br /><br /></strong>The purchase of smartphones can be carried out centrally by the Ministry of Health of the Republic of Kazakhstan within the framework of specialized procurement (based on the experience of procurement during the pandemic) among suppliers with CT-KZ.<br />You can also set a condition on the need for pre-installed applications for online consultations and other requirements for ensuring information security and personal data protection.</p>', '2022-01-26 07:56:11', '2022-02-08 04:17:52'),
