(363, 'market', 'title', 1, 'en', 'Research-overview of the smartphone market in Kazakhstan', '2022-01-27 10:25:44', '2022-02-03 08:52:06'),
(364, 'market', 'first_content', 1, 'en', '<p>Research-overview of the <strong>smartphone market in Kazakhstan</strong><br /><br />According to the Trade Map database, over the past 5 years, the import of cell phones to Kazakhstan has increased by 72% and amounted to $670 million by the end of 2020.<br /><br /><strong>The volume of smartphone imports to Kazakhstan 2016-2020, million US dollars</strong><br /><br /><br /></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://itprom.testkz.ru/storage/market/February2022/Group 7.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\n<p>According to IDC, Kazakhstan\'s mobile phone market grew by 11% in 2020 compared to 2019, reaching 4.7 million units.<br /><br />Thus, today the average price for one smartphone is about 60 thousand tenge. (excluding VAT and other payments).<br /><br />Kazakhstan is a smartphone-oriented market, and the share of push-button phones was only 9.1% of total sales.<br /><br />Smartphone shipments declined in the first half of 2020 due to the first lockdown from March to May, and then the second in July-August. The second quarter was particularly weak as retail sales moved online. With the reopening of shopping malls and stores at the end of the summer, sales recovered.<br /><br />In the third quarter, sales increased by 20.8% compared to the same period in 2019. In the fourth quarter, the market volume remained at the level of 2019.<br /><br />Scarcity is the word that can characterize 2020 for the electronics market and for almost all players.<br /><br />On the one hand, negative forecasts were made at the beginning of 2020, component suppliers adjusted to them.<br /><br />Then Huawei purchases played a role, which swept components from the market and created an additional deficit. At the planning and production stage, problems arose, and they affected all companies that do not have vertically oriented production, that is, they do not have their own key components.<br /><br />As an example, Apple can be cited, the company did not buy power chips for the 12th iPhone in advance, as a result, it was faced with the fact that it could not purchase them, as it did in previous years. The price that Apple was willing to pay for such a chip turned out to be several times lower than the average on the market.<br /><br />Among vendors, the biggest change of the year was the fall in Huawei\'s share.<br /><br />By the fourth quarter of 2020, it had dropped to 2.8% from almost a quarter of the smartphone market at the beginning of 2019, according to the study. Xiaomi has doubled its share in a year, and OPPO shipments also continue to grow rapidly.<br /><br />Apple remains a relatively small player in the market, and the impact of the 5G-enabled iPhone 12 lineup released in November has been limited.</p>', '2022-01-27 10:25:44', '2022-02-03 08:52:06'),
(365, 'market', 'second_content', 1, 'en', '<p>Top 5 smartphone manufacturing companies, supply volumes (in millions of units) and market share, Kazakhstan<br /><br /></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://itprom.testkz.ru/storage/market/February2022/Group 61.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\n<p>IDC expects the phone market to be stable this year compared to 2020, and 5G volumes will grow to one-sixth of the total number of smartphones by the last quarter.<br /><br /></p>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<p><strong>The situation in the world</strong><br /><br /></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://itprom.testkz.ru/storage/market/February2022/Group.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\n<p>Source: IDC<br /><br /></p>\n<p>More than 50% of the Kazakhstan market is accounted for by one brand &ndash; Samsung.</p>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<p><strong>The situation in the world</strong><br /><br />The global smartphone market in 2021 expects a gradual recovery and even some growth - as users get used to the \"new normal\" in the conditions of the coronavirus pandemic, according to the forecast of TrendForce analysts.<br /><br />The top 6 leaders of 2021, according to the forecast, will be located in the following sequence: Samsung, Apple, Xiaomi, OPPO, Vivo and Transsion.<br /><br />Together, these six companies will control about 80% of the global smartphone market in 2021.<br /><br />Due to the consequences of US export restrictions and the separation of the Honor brand into an independent company, Huawei expects to fall from third place to seventh in the global ranking of smartphone suppliers in 2021.</p>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<p><strong>Top 7 global smartphone suppliers and their share in the 5G market. 2020-2021, million units</strong></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://itprom.testkz.ru/storage/market/February2022/Group 17.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\n<p>Source: TrendForce</p>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<p><strong>What will affect the development of the smartphone market</strong><br /><br />The COVID-19 pandemic will remain a key factor of uncertainty in the development of the global smartphone market, as it will have a significant impact on the global economy for a long time, TrendForce notes.<br /><br />Among other factors contributing to uncertainty in this market in 2021, analysts also note possible geopolitical instability and a potential shortage of modern production capacities in the semiconductor market.<br /><br /><strong>The global era of 5G is coming</strong><br /><br />The ever-increasing penetration of 5G networks, as well as the growing range of entry- and mid-level 5G mobile processors, will have a positive impact on the development of the smartphone market.<br />In 2021, it is expected to increase the number and capacity of commercial 5G mobile networks around the world, as well as the entry of new countries into this market.<br /><br />In TrendForce, the share of global sales of 5G smartphones by the end of 2021 is projected at about 37% &ndash; up to about 500 million smartphones per year.</p>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<p>Cost and profit of the most popular smartphone models<br /><br />According to TechWalls, the average margin (profit) from the sale of smartphones is 60%.<br /><br />Below is detailed information about the cost price, taking into account all specifications and assembly, and the full retail price at the start of sales, as well as the margin (profit) for a single model.<br />Cost and profit of popular phone models</p>\n<p><img src=\"http://itprom.testkz.ru/storage/market/February2022/Group 18.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\n<p>Source: TechWalls</p>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<p>Technical specifications of popular models<br /><br />There are many ratings for evaluating smartphones. The concept of \"the best smartphone\" can be interpreted in different ways: for some it is a top flagship, and for others it is just a good device for their money.<br />In this regard, you can see a different number of ratings on the network.<br /><br />Eg:<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Top from Business Insider<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; best smartphone - iPhone 12;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; best Android Phone &ndash; Samsung Galaxy S21;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; best phone for photography - Samsung Galaxy S21 Ultra;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; the best phone in terms of battery life &ndash; Motorola Moto G Power;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; the best phone for games - Asus ROG 3;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; the best phone for kids - Google Pixel 4a;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; the best phone for less money is the iPhone SE 2020.<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Top from top5.co.ua<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No. 1 Apple iPhone Smartphone - Editor\'s Choice<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No. 2 Samsung Galaxy Note - Buyer\'s Choice<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No. 3 Smartphone HONOR - The Best Reviews<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No. 4Xiaomi Mi 10 Lite - The Best Inexpensive<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No. 5 HUAWEI Y8P Smartphone - The Best Cameras<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No. 6 Xiaomi Redmi 4X 32GB - The Best Compact<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No. 7 ZTE Blade A7 (2020) 3/64GB - Best Cameras<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No. 8 Samsung Galaxy A20 - The Best Brand<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No. 9 vivo V17 Neo 128GB - Best Screen<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No. 10 HONOR 30 - Best Design<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Top of the Tech Rating<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The best smartphones in the price/quality ratio<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Samsung A51<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Xiaomi Redmi Note 8 Pro<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Samsung M31<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Xiaomi Roso X3<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Realme 6 Pro<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The best Chinese smartphones<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Honor 30 Pro+<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Xiaomi Mi Note 10 Pro<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Huawei P40 Pro<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; OnePlus 8 Pro<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Xiaomi Mi 10 Pro<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The best branded smartphones<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Google Pixel 5<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Asus ROG Phone 3<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Samsung Note 20 Ultra<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Apple iPhone 12 Pro Max<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Samsung Galaxy S21 Ultra<br /><br />At the same time, there are options in the choice of smartphones for which certain purchases are made:<br /><br />1. OS selection.<br />Android or iOS? This choice depends on the personal preferences of the buyer.<br /><br />2. The purpose of using a smartphone.<br />If the user is a gamer, then a smartphone with a powerful processor is selected. If a photographer, then the number of megapixels and the power of the GPU are studied. Also the capabilities of secondary sensors, etc.<br /><br />From the technical characteristics in the bulk , it is taken into account:<br />-Screen<br />-Cameras<br />-Processor<br />-RAM<br />- Memory<br />-Battery<br /><br />Bonuses:<br /><br />-Protection from water;<br />-Adaptation to a bank card and the possibility of contactless payment;<br />-Support for two SIM cards registered with different mobile operators at the same time;<br />-Fast wireless charging.<br /><br />Next, a selection was made from flagships and budget models to determine the portrait of the optimal smartphone.<img src=\"http://itprom.testkz.ru/storage/market/February2022/Group 60.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\n<p>Source: Chip<br />Calculations: ITProm</p>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<p>So, based on the data obtained, the portrait of the optimal smartphone looks like this:<br /><br />This device is equipped with: a 6.6-inch screen, 4 cameras, Qualcomm Snapdragon or MediaTek Helio processors, the amount of RAM is 6 GB, the amount of memory is 128 GB, the battery capacity is within 4436 mAh.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2022-01-27 10:25:44', '2022-02-03 08:52:06'),
(366, 'market', 'third_content', 1, 'en', '<p>Threats and <strong>market trends</strong><br /><br />According to the message mydrivers.com , there is a crisis in the supply of microchips in the world at the moment.<br /><br />This crisis has affected not only smartphones, but also other industries, including the automotive industry, computers and game consoles.<br /><br />At the same time, smartphone manufacturers can use this circumstance to raise prices for their flagship models.<br /><br />Mydrivers.com assumes that the cost of flagships of Chinese brands will increase due to several factors:<br /><br />- the pandemic and the crisis have led to an increase in smartphone sales, which means that the global market has sufficient and even excessive demand.<br /><br />- the prices of competitors are much higher, then the increase in the cost of smartphones from Chinese brands will allow them to maintain positions in the market and get more profit, the fact that the most advanced models (flagships) have characteristics that are often not inferior to expensive brands allows companies to raise prices.<br /><br />This creates an image of a top-class brand for their product. As a result, using the manufacturing crisis as a basis for rising prices, smartphone developers in China can gradually increase the cost of their smartphones.<br /><br /><br /><strong>Recent landmark industry events</strong><br /><br />- LG completely stops the development and production of smartphones. Their release will be curtailed on July 31, 2021 &ndash; the company could not withstand competition from Samsung, Apple, Xiaomi and other strong players. LG will focus on other areas of activity, including the Internet of things, artificial intelligence and technologies for electric vehicles.<br /><br />- Huawei halves smartphone production. The year 2021 will be one of the worst in Huawei\'s history in terms of smartphone shipments. The company is reducing production and this is just the beginning. Huawei\'s smartphone sales declined after the company had to remove Google\'s mobile services from its devices due to US sanctions.<br /><br />Sales were also affected by the decision of the US authorities to ban all companies using American technologies from working with Huawei, which is why the manufacturer lost access to most of its suppliers, including Qualcomm, TSMC and Samsung. As a result, Huawei, which previously ranked second in the global mobile market after Samsung, failed to enter the top five smartphone manufacturers by the end of 2020. In addition, Huawei was forced to sell its successful Honor sub-brand at the end of last year in order to withdraw it from the impact of US sanctions.<br /><br /><br /><strong>Conclusions:</strong><br /><br />- Market stability. The smartphone market in Kazakhstan has great potential due to the constant stable demand.<br />Over the past 5 years, the import of cell phones to Kazakhstan has increased by 72%.<br /><br />- The coronavirus could not stop the growth of the smartphone market. The domestic mobile phone market grew by 11% in 2020 compared to 2019.<br /><br />- Budget-oriented client. The average price for one smartphone is 60 thousand tenge. (excluding VAT and other payments).<br /><br />- The dominance of one brand. The Samsung brand occupies more than 50% of the smartphone market in Kazakhstan.<br /><br />- Investment attractiveness of the sector. According to TechWalls, the average margin (profit) from the sale of smartphones is 60%.<br /><br />- Portrait of the optimal smartphone: 6.6-inch screen, 4 cameras, Qualcomm Snapdragon or MediaTek Helio processors, 6 GB RAM, 128 GB memory, battery capacity within 4436 mAh.<br /><br />- No warranty for the manufacturer. Even global players with a glorious history are leaving the market. LG completely stops the development and production of smartphones from July 31, 2021.</p>', '2022-01-27 10:25:44', '2022-02-03 08:52:06'),
